-- Southwest Airlines posts quarterly profit
-- 
-- Thu Jul 24, 2008 7:45am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/07/24/us-southwest-idUSWNAB230720080724

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Southwest Airlines Co ( LUV.N ), which has a history of successfully hedging against high fuel costs, on Thursday posted a quarterly profit. 

 Second-quarter net income rose to $321 million, or 44 cents a share, from $278 million, or 36 cents per share, a year earlier. Excluding special items, earnings fell to $121 million, or 16 cents per share, from $195 million, or 25 cents per share. (Reporting by  Mark McSherry ; Editing by Lisa Von Ahn)